<treatmentCitationGroup id="66BF7060074891044F91FDF7FDFFFD57" pageId="13" pageNumber="564">
<treatmentCitation id="C70E715F074891044F91FDF7FE28FDCA" author="HRABE S." box="[132,492,557,581]" page="271" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" year="1960">
<taxonomicName id="81AF2CCD074891044F91FDF7FE28FDCA" authority="Hrabe, 1960: 271" authorityName="Hrabe" authorityPageNumber="271" authorityYear="1960" box="[132,492,557,581]" class="Clitellata" family="Lumbriculidae" genus="Trichodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lumbriculida" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tenuis">
<emphasis id="74DB8B5C074891044F91FDF7FEF7FDCA" box="[132,307,557,581]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="564">Trichodrilus tenuis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="223E2ABF074891044E2CFDF7FE28FDCA" author="HRABE S." box="[313,492,557,581]" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" pagination="245 - 277" refId="ref15683" refString="HRABE S. 1960. - Oligochaeta limicola from the collection of Dr S. Husmann. Publ Fac Sci Univ Brno 415: 245 - 277." type="journal article" year="1960">Hrabě, 1960: 271</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
. MATERIAL EXAMINED. — Many mature, mated specimens, IRScNB, I.G. 32392, station 1 (slides 11.006.04, 11.007.01, vial AB31536635), station 2 (slides 11.032.01, 11.032.02, vials AB31536765, AB31536719, AB31515927, AB31536665), station 15 (slide 11.252.01, vial AB31525637).
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0EB504C5074891044F91FD2CFDA1F883" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4610574E074891044F91FD2CFF2CFC81" blockId="13.[130,777,758,1804]" box="[132,232,758,784]" pageId="13" pageNumber="564">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4610574E074891044F91FCCFFD33FBC1" blockId="13.[130,777,758,1804]" pageId="13" pageNumber="564">
All these fragments probably belong to the same species, which can be ascribed to 
<taxonomicName id="81AF2CCD074891044E87FCEFFDF5FCDF" box="[402,561,821,848]" class="Clitellata" family="Lumbriculidae" genus="Trichodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lumbriculida" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="74DB8B5C074891044E87FCEFFDCBFCC0" box="[402,527,821,847]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="564">Trichodrilus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
group II 
<emphasis id="74DB8B5C074891044D83FCECFD0EFCC0" box="[662,714,822,847]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="564">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="223E2ABF074891044DC5FCEFFEB3FCE0" author="RODRIGUEZ P. &amp; GIANI N." pageId="13" pageNumber="564" pagination="35 - 51" refId="ref16613" refString="RODRIGUEZ P. &amp; GIANI N. 1994. - A preliminary review of the taxonomic characters used for the systematics of the genus Trichodrilus Claparede (Oligochaeta, Lumbriculidae). Hydrobiologia 278: 35 - 51." type="journal article" year="1994">Rodriguez &amp; Giani (1994)</bibRefCitation>
. This group of species is characterized by pear-shaped or spherical atria, not laterally compressed, all setae more or less alike, unmodified penial setae, two pairs of spermathecae in XI and XII, and posterior vasa deferentia penetrating into XI. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="223E2ABF074891044EF2FC0EFCC6FC60" author="RODRIGUEZ P. &amp; GIANI N." box="[487,770,980,1007]" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" pagination="35 - 51" refId="ref16613" refString="RODRIGUEZ P. &amp; GIANI N. 1994. - A preliminary review of the taxonomic characters used for the systematics of the genus Trichodrilus Claparede (Oligochaeta, Lumbriculidae). Hydrobiologia 278: 35 - 51." type="journal article" year="1994">Rodriguez &amp; Giani (1994)</bibRefCitation>
, the species within this group can barely be separated due to the variability of diagnostic characters within populations, or even to incorrect diagnoses in the original descriptions.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4610574E074891044F8EFB8EFCC2F903" blockId="13.[130,777,758,1804]" pageId="13" pageNumber="564">
Our specimens have no lateral blood vessels in posterior segments, a character shared among this group by 
<taxonomicName id="81AF2CCD074891044D91FBAFFECAFB21" authority="Hrabe, 1938" authorityName="Hrabe" authorityYear="1938" class="Clitellata" family="Lumbriculidae" genus="Trichodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lumbriculida" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="claparedei">
<emphasis id="74DB8B5C074891044D91FBAFFCC3FB01" box="[644,775,1140,1166]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="564">T. claparedei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="223E2ABF074891044F91FB4EFECAFB21" author="HRABE S." box="[132,270,1172,1198]" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" pagination="73 - 85" refId="ref15661" refString="HRABE S. 1938. - Trichodrilus moravicus et claparedei, neue Lumbriculidae. Zoologischer Anzeiger 121: 73 - 85." type="journal article" year="1938">Hrabě, 1938</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="81AF2CCD074891044E0EFB4FFDC5FB21" authority="Cook, 1967" authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1967" box="[283,513,1172,1198]" class="Clitellata" family="Lumbriculidae" genus="Trichodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lumbriculida" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hrabei">
<emphasis id="74DB8B5C074891044E0EFB4FFEB3FB21" box="[283,375,1172,1198]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="564">T. hrabei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="223E2ABF074891044E6AFB4EFDC5FB21" author="COOK D. G." box="[383,513,1172,1198]" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" pagination="353 - 368" refId="ref14253" refString="COOK D. G. 1967. - Studies on the Lumbriculidae (Oligochaeta) in Britain. Journal of Zoology, Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London 153: 353 - 368." type="journal article" year="1967">Cook, 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="81AF2CCD074891044D1BFB4FFCC7FB21" authority="Hrabe, 1960" authorityName="Hrabe" authorityYear="1960" box="[526,771,1172,1198]" class="Clitellata" family="Lumbriculidae" genus="Trichodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lumbriculida" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="medius">
<emphasis id="74DB8B5C074891044D1BFB4FFDB5FB21" box="[526,625,1172,1198]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="564">T. medius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="223E2ABF074891044D6CFB4EFCC7FB21" author="HRABE S." box="[633,771,1172,1198]" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" pagination="245 - 277" refId="ref15683" refString="HRABE S. 1960. - Oligochaeta limicola from the collection of Dr S. Husmann. Publ Fac Sci Univ Brno 415: 245 - 277." type="journal article" year="1960">Hrabě, 1960</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="81AF2CCD074891044F93FB6FFE57FB41" authority="Hrabe, 1937" authorityName="Hrabe" authorityYear="1937" box="[134,403,1204,1230]" class="Clitellata" family="Lumbriculidae" genus="Trichodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lumbriculida" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="moravicus">
<emphasis id="74DB8B5C074891044F93FB6FFEC1FB41" box="[134,261,1205,1230]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="564">T. moravicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="223E2ABF074891044E19FB6EFE57FB41" author="HRABE S." box="[268,403,1204,1230]" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref15614" refString="HRABE S. 1937. - Etudes biospeologiques (1). V. Contribution a l'etude du genre Trichodrilus (Oligoch., Lumbriculidae) et description de deux especes nouvelles. Bulletin du Musee royal d'Histoire naturelle de Belgique XIII: 1 - 23." type="journal article" year="1937">Hrabě, 1937</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="81AF2CCD074891044E8AFB6FFDBCFB41" authority="Timm, 1979" authorityName="Timm" authorityYear="1979" box="[415,632,1204,1230]" class="Clitellata" family="Lumbriculidae" genus="Trichodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lumbriculida" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="seirei">
<emphasis id="74DB8B5C074891044E8AFB6FFE2FFB41" box="[415,491,1205,1230]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="564">T. seirei</emphasis>
Timm, 1979
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="81AF2CCD074891044DA4FB6FFEC8FB61" authority="Hrabe, 1960" authorityName="Hrabe" authorityYear="1960" class="Clitellata" family="Lumbriculidae" genus="Trichodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lumbriculida" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tenuis">
<emphasis id="74DB8B5C074891044DA4FB6FFCC3FB41" box="[689,775,1205,1230]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="564">T. tenuis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="223E2ABF074891044F91FB0EFEC8FB61" author="HRABE S." box="[132,268,1236,1262]" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" pagination="245 - 277" refId="ref15683" refString="HRABE S. 1960. - Oligochaeta limicola from the collection of Dr S. Husmann. Publ Fac Sci Univ Brno 415: 245 - 277." type="journal article" year="1960">Hrabě, 1960</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Our specimens can be characterized by spherical to ovoid atrial ampullae, 55-80 µm long, 54-68 µm wide, with thin muscle layer (2.5-4.0 µm thick), and distinct proximal ducts, which make them the closest to 
<taxonomicName id="81AF2CCD074891044D18FAEEFDA5FAC2" authorityName="Hrabe" authorityYear="1960" box="[525,609,1332,1357]" class="Clitellata" family="Lumbriculidae" genus="Trichodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lumbriculida" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tenuis">
<emphasis id="74DB8B5C074891044D18FAEEFDA5FAC2" box="[525,609,1332,1357]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="564">T. tenuis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, atrial ampullae are entirely covered by high prostate cells, and ducts are half the size of diameter of ampullae, ending in small conical, external penes. In 
<taxonomicName id="81AF2CCD074891044E7FFA4EFE7AFA22" authorityName="Hrabe" authorityYear="1960" box="[362,446,1428,1453]" class="Clitellata" family="Lumbriculidae" genus="Trichodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lumbriculida" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tenuis">
<emphasis id="74DB8B5C074891044E7FFA4EFE7AFA22" box="[362,446,1428,1453]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="564">T. tenuis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, atrial ampullae bear high prostate cells only in their distal part, ducts are very short, and end with minute porophores. 
<bibRefCitation id="223E2ABF074891044E85FA09FD15FA62" author="JUGET J. &amp; DES CHATELLIERS M. C." box="[400,721,1491,1517]" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" pagination="23 - 28" refId="ref15752" refString="JUGET J. &amp; DES CHATELLIERS M. C. 2001. - Taxonomical survey of some stygobiont oligochaetes from the eastern part of France, including description of a new species. Hydrobiologia 463: 23 - 28." type="journal article" year="2001">Juget &amp; des Châtelliers (2001)</bibRefCitation>
have described a peculiar structure of the spermathecae in material from the Lyon area (
<collectingCountry id="3EB817DE074891044E43F9C9FE5AF9A2" box="[342,414,1555,1581]" name="France" pageId="13" pageNumber="564">France</collectingCountry>
) ascribed to 
<taxonomicName id="81AF2CCD074891044D37F9C9FDB3F9A3" authorityName="Hrabe" authorityYear="1960" box="[546,631,1555,1580]" class="Clitellata" family="Lumbriculidae" genus="Trichodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lumbriculida" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tenuis">
<emphasis id="74DB8B5C074891044D37F9C9FDB3F9A3" box="[546,631,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="564">T. tenuis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in which the proximal part of ampulla (wrongly indicated as the distal part) is differentiated into a so-called “pseudovestibule” at junction with spermathecal ducts. Such a structure is not seen on our material.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4610574E074891044F8EF948FDA1F883" blockId="13.[130,777,758,1804]" pageId="13" pageNumber="564">
This is probably a new species but its description would ideally lie within a revision of 
<taxonomicName id="81AF2CCD074891044EDEF968FDAFF942" box="[459,619,1714,1741]" class="Clitellata" family="Lumbriculidae" genus="Trichodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lumbriculida" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="74DB8B5C074891044EDEF968FD8CF943" box="[459,584,1714,1740]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="564">Trichodrilus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
group II 
<emphasis id="74DB8B5C074891044DC6F969FCC3F943" box="[723,775,1715,1740]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="564">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="223E2ABF074891044F91F908FE67F963" author="RODRIGUEZ P. &amp; GIANI N." box="[132,419,1746,1772]" pageId="13" pageNumber="564" pagination="35 - 51" refId="ref16613" refString="RODRIGUEZ P. &amp; GIANI N. 1994. - A preliminary review of the taxonomic characters used for the systematics of the genus Trichodrilus Claparede (Oligochaeta, Lumbriculidae). Hydrobiologia 278: 35 - 51." type="journal article" year="1994">Rodriguez &amp; Giani (1994)</bibRefCitation>
, based on additional material and genetic characterization via DNA barcoding.
</paragraph>
